      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DUBBO BOY (2) nice gelding who overcome the wide draw for a dominant victory over 1000m at Warren in the soft (7) going. Maps to get the gun run and can keep the winning momentum going with the tongue-tie going on. SELHURST PARK (8) races best with his runs spaced and has a good record on his home track. Up in class from the sticky gate when he chipped away late to finish seventh over 1205m at the Sapphire Coast in BM66 grade. Good run here two-back and can run a bold race. CHEMTRAIL (1) capable Highway horse who can return to winning form second-up. Showed good early speed from the outside draw before tiring to run twelfth over 1100m at Randwick in Highway class. Proven second-up and ticks plenty of boxes today. EAGERLY AWAITS (5) in need of the run first-up when eighth over 1000m at Wyon. Blinkers go on and has placed second up. ",
